==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mutinous
<hw>Mu"ti*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Mutiny</er>.]</ety> <def>Disposed to mutiny; in a state of mutiny;
characterized by mutiny; seditious; insubordinate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The city was becoming <qex>mutinous</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Mu"ti*nous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mu"ti*nous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mutiny</ent>⟦br⟧
